---
description: User-facing copy must not use em dashes; remove them when editing.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Copy: no em dashes

- Do not use the em dash character (Unicode U+2014) in any user-visible string: UI labels, alerts, notifications, modal body text, tooltips, or empty states.
- When you touch a file for other work, replace any em dashes in user-facing strings in that file with shorter punctuation (period, comma, colon, or parentheses) or split into two sentences.
- Code comments and internal docs may use normal hyphens (-) where needed; keep comments readable without em dashes when you edit them.
